HEADWORD: Ancipitous
<hw>An*cip"i*tous</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>anceps</ets>,
<ets>ancipitis</ets>, two-headed, double; <ets>an-</ets> for
<ets>amb-</ets> on both sides + <ets>caput</ets> head.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Two-edged instead of round; -- said of certain
flattened stems, as those of blue grass, and rarely also of
leaves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ancistroid</ent>⟦br⟧
